Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula briefed the media on COVID-19 lockdown regulations and directives related to transport. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says Prasa is not ready to resume the Metrorail commuter services. This will have to wait another month. "Prasa was ready to go on Monday, but we can't take that risk, because you know there are thousands and thousands of commuters who depend on that. Equally the number of people going to work as much as they increase, they are not fully 100% so to say, so it has enabled us in terms of our planning to ensure that we utilise June to get ready,” he said. SA Lockdown: Mbalula takes aim at Rea Vaya bus services Mbalula said the revised target date for the resumption of Metrorail services is now 1 July on the following lines: Long distance trains remain prohibited. Mbalula briefed the media on COVID-19 lockdown regulations and directives related to transport on Saturday afternoon. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.